title Transportation Logistics Landscape
style wardley

// Anchors (users) at the top of the value chain.
// The Public is the primary end-user; Producers and Government are
// secondary anchors since the scenario explicitly names them as actors.
anchor The Public [0.97, 0.60] label [10, -6]
anchor Producers [0.94, 0.48] label [-70, -6]
anchor Government [0.95, 0.32] label [-78, -6]

// Retail / commerce surface — what the public physically or digitally touches.
component Shops [0.88, 0.80] label [-28, -10]
component E-commerce [0.86, 0.68] label [10, -4]

// User-facing supply chain capabilities
component Delivery [0.80, 0.58] label [10, 0]
component Real-Time Stock [0.74, 0.30] label [10, 0]
component Supply Chain Awareness [0.78, 0.18] label [10, -4]

// Core physical flow
component Last Mile [0.66, 0.48] label [10, 0]
component Long Haul [0.60, 0.80] label [10, 0]
component Logistics Hubs [0.54, 0.62] label [10, 0]
component Warehouses & Storage [0.48, 0.82] label [10, 0]

// Vehicle / power layer
component Trucks (HGV) [0.38, 0.80] label [10, 0]
component Automated Delivery [0.34, 0.18] label [10, -4]
component Drones & Scouts [0.30, 0.12] label [10, 0]
component Powertrain (Fossil/Electric) [0.26, 0.60] label [10, 0]

// Information layer — shared data utility feeding real-time stock & awareness
component Traffic & Telematics Data [0.42, 0.70] label [10, 0]

// Topology
component Cities [0.22, 0.86] label [10, 0]
component Rural Areas [0.20, 0.72] label [10, 0]

// Enablers — regulation, sovereignty, skills
component Regulation [0.14, 0.66] label [10, 0]
component HGV Skills [0.44, 0.40] label [10, 0] inertia
component Sovereignty (CNI/Territorial) [0.10, 0.24] label [10, 0] inertia

// Dependencies — anchors to needs
The Public->Shops
The Public->E-commerce
The Public->Supply Chain Awareness
Producers->Long Haul
Producers->Warehouses & Storage
Government->Regulation
Government->Sovereignty (CNI/Territorial)

// Commerce surface -> capabilities
Shops->Delivery
Shops->Real-Time Stock
E-commerce->Delivery
E-commerce->Real-Time Stock

// Capabilities -> physical flow
Delivery->Last Mile
Delivery->Long Haul
Last Mile->Logistics Hubs
Long Haul->Logistics Hubs
Logistics Hubs->Warehouses & Storage
Real-Time Stock->Traffic & Telematics Data
Supply Chain Awareness->Traffic & Telematics Data

// Physical flow -> vehicle layer
Last Mile->Trucks (HGV)
Last Mile->Automated Delivery
Last Mile->Drones & Scouts
Long Haul->Trucks (HGV)
Long Haul->Automated Delivery
Automated Delivery->Drones & Scouts

// Vehicle layer -> power
Trucks (HGV)->Powertrain (Fossil/Electric)
Automated Delivery->Powertrain (Fossil/Electric)
Drones & Scouts->Powertrain (Fossil/Electric)

// Information layer feeds vehicles
Trucks (HGV)->Traffic & Telematics Data
Automated Delivery->Traffic & Telematics Data

// Topology constrains the physical flow
Last Mile->Cities
Last Mile->Rural Areas
Logistics Hubs->Cities

// Skills & regulation
Trucks (HGV)->HGV Skills
Long Haul->HGV Skills
Long Haul->Regulation
Warehouses & Storage->Regulation
Logistics Hubs->Sovereignty (CNI/Territorial)
Warehouses & Storage->Sovereignty (CNI/Territorial)

// Evolution arrows — where market forces push rightward
evolve Last Mile 0.72
evolve Automated Delivery 0.55
evolve Drones & Scouts 0.42
evolve Real-Time Stock 0.72
evolve Powertrain (Fossil/Electric) 0.82
evolve Traffic & Telematics Data 0.85
evolve Supply Chain Awareness 0.50
evolve Shops 0.90

// Strategic notes
annotation 1 [[0.48, 0.88]] Long-haul, warehousing, and shops behave as commoditised utility
annotation 2 [[0.32, 0.15]] Automated delivery / drones: Genesis/Custom-Built, poised to evolve
annotation 3 [[0.10, 0.24]] Sovereignty + CNI concerns are the main source of inertia
annotation 4 [[0.44, 0.40]] HGV skills shortage: Product-stage activity stuck behind a scarce resource

// Build/buy/outsource guidance
build Automated Delivery
build Supply Chain Awareness
buy Traffic & Telematics Data
buy Real-Time Stock
buy Powertrain (Fossil/Electric)
outsource Long Haul
outsource Warehouses & Storage
